name: songs my mother taught me
description:
childhood memories, both conscious and subconscious, explain many of our responses, both conscious and subconscious, to the content of our lives. Even the very content of our lives.

like birds that fly in flamboyant colours, the songs my mother taught me dance around in their resounding flair, look upon me with endless compassion, hold my hand, hold me in their arms. A refuge, a curse, a blessing.

A generative piece by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro.
Made with Processing, 5000x5000px png.
